metadata.name: NEWWYork
metadata.description:
City lights touch my skin
I glow and shine
And I always sin.
The city is where my heart stays
Even when I live so far,
My heart sings for the noise
My eyes search for the stars.
Strangers pass, we don't speak 
And our eyes never meet.
I visit the big city
To feel beautiful and pretty
To see the vastness that we have
To feel the history of souls that have passed.
You see, these city streets
They talk to me
Confirm my bias that
We should laugh and play
And never, ever sleep.
When life moves so fast
I reflect while walking on the street,
I ache for the memories that are past
Knowing I will only love this city, my biggest feat.
